Windmere Corp. said it exercised an option to buy an additional 10% of the issued and outstanding shares of Catalina Lighting Inc., boosting its stake in the Miami-based lighting fixtures concern to 17.9%. 

Under terms of the transaction, Windmere swapped 238,493 of its common shares for 505,044 shares of Catalina.
Windmere, which makes personal-care products, has about 15.5 million shares outstanding following the transaction. 

